\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Where Claude genuinely outperforms a local 7B\'9614B model
\f1\b0 \cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Reasoning and nuance.
\f1\b0 \'a0For complex tasks \'97 synthesizing a long email thread, making judgment calls about document organization, writing something that requires real craft \'97 Claude Sonnet or Opus will produce noticeably better output than a local Qwen 8B. The quality gap is real for anything requiring subtle understanding.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Long, complex documents.
\f1\b0 \'a0Claude handles 200K token context windows. Your local model on 16GB is comfortable up to maybe 8\'9616K tokens depending on the model. For analyzing a long contract, a full year of journal entries, or a large financial statement, Claude wins handily.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Instruction following.
\f1\b0 \'a0Claude is significantly more reliable at following precise formatting instructions, structured output requirements, and multi-step tasks. This matters a lot for document automation where you need consistent, predictable output.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Writing quality.
\f1\b0 \'a0For anything you'd actually share \'97 a polished summary, a drafted letter, a formatted project log \'97 Claude's output requires less cleanup.\cb1 \
\

\f2\b \cb3 Where local wins
\f1\b0 \cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Privacy.
\f1\b0 \'a0Anything touching your financial data, personal communications, health notes, or Anny's family information stays off Anthropic's servers entirely. That was your original motivation and it's a legitimate one.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Cost at volume.
\f1\b0 \'a0If you're running nightly batch jobs \'97 processing 50 emails, scanning 20 documents \'97 the token costs on Claude API add up. Local is free regardless of volume.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Speed for simple tasks.
\f1\b0 \'a0For quick classification, tagging, or short summarization, a local model responds in seconds with zero network latency.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Always available.
\f1\b0 \'a0No internet required, no API outages, no rate limits.\cb1 \
\

