\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 What Amazon does and doesn't offer
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Amazon's official Orders API exists but it's exclusively for\'a0
\f2\b sellers
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 businesses managing their own Amazon storefronts. It provides a live transaction feed of seller activity, not consumer purchase history.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://docs.openbridge.com/en/articles/6304068-amazon-orders-api-connector"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
