\f2\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb3 The Ollama-specific intelligence layer\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 This is where local LLM really shines for personal finance. Ollama does three things that commercial APIs can't do cheaply or privately:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 1. Payee normalization
\f1\b0 \'a0Banks send messy strings like "SQ *BLUE BOTTLE COF 4155551234 CA" \'97 Ollama cleans these to "Blue Bottle Coffee" based on your existing YNAB payee list, avoiding duplicates.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 2. Category learning from your history
\f1\b0 \'a0Feed Ollama a sample of your last 6 months of categorized transactions as a reference. It learns that Safeway is "Groceries", Shell is "Transportation: Gas", your specific dentist goes to "Medical", etc. This context stays local.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 3. Anomaly detection
\f1\b0 \'a0Ollama flags when something unusual happens \'97 "this is a new payee", "this is 3x your typical grocery spend", "you haven't been to this category in 6 months." More nuanced than rule-based checks.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

