\f2\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb3 The Amazon reconciliation problem\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 The core challenge: YNAB sees "AMZN Mktp US*AB1CD2EF3" for $47.83, but has no idea whether that was dog food, a drill bit, or a birthday gift. For retirement spending visibility, this matters a lot because Amazon often becomes 10\'9620% of household spending and opaque categorization defeats the purpose of budgeting.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

