\f2\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb3 What this means for your specific use case\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 Your planned setup \'97 YNAB tokens, Gmail OAuth, bank transaction data, Amazon order history, daily messaging integration \'97 is legitimately high-value for an attacker. A compromised OpenClaw with those credentials could:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls29\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Drain accounts via YNAB's transaction POST capability (no, YNAB can't move money, but it could corrupt your financial records significantly)\cb1 \
\ls29\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Read every email including password resets, 2FA codes, banking notices\cb1 \
\ls29\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Impersonate you to family and contacts\cb1 \
\ls29\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Exfiltrate years of personal data\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 This isn't theoretical paranoia \'97 it's the actual threat model you'd be accepting.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb3 The practical defensive stack\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 Here's what a hardened deployment actually looks like for your use case:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Network isolation (most important)
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bind the gateway to 127.0.0.1 \'97 never to 0.0.0.0. Keep the Control UI off any untrusted network.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blink.new/blog/openclaw-security-best-practices-2026"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 Blink\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0For remote access from your iPhone or van, use Tailscale's encrypted mesh rather than opening ports. This alone eliminates most of the realistic attack surface.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Update discipline
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Subscribe to the OpenClaw releases RSS feed and update within a few days of any security release. Given the active threat landscape, auto-update if possible. A machine running a version with a known CVE for months is the typical victim profile.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

