\ls40\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 A plain Python finance job
\f1\b0 \'a0(no messaging, no email reading, no web browsing, just YNAB API and Ollama for categorization)\cb1 \
\ls40\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 An OpenClaw user-facing layer
\f1\b0 \'a0(read-only access to your local finance database, no YNAB credentials, handles messaging and queries)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You cut off most attack paths:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls41\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Email prompt injection 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  reaches only the user-facing layer, which can't write to YNAB\cb1 \
\ls41\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Malicious skill 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  reaches only the user-facing layer, which has no credentials\cb1 \
\ls41\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Community skill compromise 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  can't pivot to the trusted tier\cb1 \
\ls41\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Prompt injection via Amazon emails 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  affects categorization suggestions but your review step catches anything weird before it posts\cb1 \
