\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 Awesome Agents\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0This is where local models become genuinely capable assistants rather than specialized tools. Retirement finance analysis, drafting emails to your accountant, handling ambiguous multi-account transactions, reasoning about tax implications \'97 32B handles these reliably.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 70B \'97 the current frontier for consumer hardware
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Llama 3.3 70B is the best general-purpose open-source model available if you have the hardware to run it. Its performance on reasoning, coding, instruction following, and long-context tasks is competitive with GPT-4o on most benchmarks, and it supports a 128K context window.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://mljourney.com/best-open-source-llms-in-2026-a-practical-guide-by-use-case/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 ML Journey\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 At 70B you're getting output quality approaching what you'd get from Claude or GPT-4o a year ago. For sensitive retirement financial reasoning \'97 where you want the model's analysis to actually be trustworthy \'97 this is the tier that matters.\cb1 \
