\cb3 Hermes Agent is a genuinely interesting project \'97 and honestly, for your specific situation, it might be a better fit than OpenClaw. Let me lay it out properly.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb3 What Hermes Agent actually is\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 Hermes Agent is an open-source AI agent framework from Nous Research, first released February 25, 2026. It runs on your own server, stores conversations persistently, automatically creates new skills from solved tasks, and is freely self-hostable.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.innobu.com/en/articles/hermes-agent-self-improvement-open-source-2026.html"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 innobu\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 It's a direct competitor to OpenClaw from Nous Research \'97 the same group that produced the Hermes family of open-source models. It was released a few months after OpenClaw and seems to have deliberately learned from OpenClaw's problems.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb3 What makes Hermes useful for home tasks\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 The "closed learning loop"
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Hermes has an agent-curated memory with periodic nudges, autonomous skill creation, skill self-improvement during use, FTS5 cross-session recall with LLM summarization, and Honcho dialectic user modeling.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 Nousresearch\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The practical effect: it learns patterns from your usage. When you correct a transaction categorization three times the same way, it stops asking. When you frequently send similar types of messages, it proposes a skill to automate them. For a retirement setup where you'll refine behavior over months, this matters.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Built for home scenarios
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Hermes supports CLI, Telegram, Discord, Slack, WhatsApp, Signal, Matrix, Mattermost, Email, SMS, BlueBubbles, Home Assistant \'97 15+ platforms from one gateway. Built-in cron with delivery to any platform. Open standard skills compatible with agentskills.io.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 Nousresearch\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Notice\'a0
\f2\b BlueBubbles
\f1\b0 \'a0in that list \'97 that's the iMessage bridge for Mac. So Hermes officially supports iMessage integration on your Mac mini, which matters since that's why you're on Apple hardware. It also supports Home Assistant directly, which pairs well with your smart-home interests.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Better security posture
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 OpenClaw has more reach with 345,000 GitHub stars but faced nine CVEs in March 2026 including CVE-2026-25253 with CVSS 8.8, plus the ClawHavoc supply chain attack with 341 malicious skills. Hermes Agent is smaller with 118 curated skills, free of known CVEs so far, and more focused on learning architecture and security.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.innobu.com/en/articles/hermes-agent-self-improvement-open-source-2026.html"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 innobu\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Hermes explicitly designed in security measures OpenClaw retrofit. Skills come from four trust tiers: Builtin (ships with Hermes, can't be tampered with), Official (published by Nous, security-audited), and two community tiers with progressively less vetting.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://hermesatlas.com/guide/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 Hermes Atlas\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 PII redaction
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 When redact_pii is true, the gateway redacts personally identifiable information from the system prompt before sending it to the LLM on supported platforms \'97 Telegram, WhatsApp, Signal.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/user-guide/configuration/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 Nousresearch\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0This is a real feature that matters if you use any cloud model for non-sensitive tasks while keeping sensitive data on Ollama.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb3 What Hermes would be useful for in your home setup\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 Given your 24GB Mac mini and everything we've discussed, here's where Hermes fits:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Personal knowledge assistant
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The self-improving memory means you can feed it information about your household over time \'97 your preferences, Anny's family context, your van's specs, your ongoing projects \'97 and it builds a usable model of your life. Ask it things and it pulls relevant context automatically.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 The ad-hoc query layer we discussed
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Remember the architecture we landed on: plain Python scripts doing the scheduled finance work, with a thin conversational layer for when you want to ask ad-hoc questions. Hermes is genuinely well-designed for that thin layer. It would sit on top of your Python-managed SQLite database and answer questions about it conversationally.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Multi-platform messaging without iMessage dependency
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 If you decide later that Telegram or Signal is more reliable than the BlueBubbles iMessage bridge (which can be finicky), Hermes handles the switch without rearchitecting anything. Same skills, different channel.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Scheduled tasks with proactive delivery
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Built-in cron with delivery to any platform.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 Nousresearch\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0Morning digests, weekly reviews, monthly retirement checks \'97 all schedulable, all deliverable to whichever chat platform you're using.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Home Assistant integration without extra skills
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Home Assistant is listed as a first-class platform in the gateway, not a skill add-on.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 Nousresearch\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0So smart home control stays simple \'97 no scraping community skills of unknown quality.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb3 Honest caveats\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 It's new
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Documentation is incomplete, the community is young, and API stability between v0.x releases is not guaranteed.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.innobu.com/en/articles/hermes-agent-self-improvement-open-source-2026.html"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 innobu\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0You'd be an early adopter. For a retirement tool meant to run for years, there's a real risk of API churn and breaking changes.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Smaller skill ecosystem
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 643 community-contributed skills in the Hub as of April 2026\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://hermesatlas.com/guide/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs18 \cf6 \cb1 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 Hermes Atlas\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \'a0versus OpenClaw's 13,000+. You're more likely to need to build things yourself. But given your Python background and the design we landed on, that may actually be a feature.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 The learning features may be more than you need
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The autonomous skill creation and dialectic user modeling are impressive, but for scheduled finance automation, they're overkill. You might not use the fancy parts at all.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

